<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{paul, swallowing eagerly.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{annie, watching him, sympathetically.}
<C>__{annie}
<D>__{your legs just sing grand opera when you move, don't they?}
<P>__{(paul says nothing, but his pain is clear)}
<D>__{it's not going to hurt forever, paul, i promise you.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{will i be able to walk?}
<C>__{annie}
<D>__{of course you will. and your arm will be fine, too. your shoulder was dislocated pretty badly, but i finally popped it back in there.}
<P>__{(proudly)}
<D>__{but what i'm most proud of is the work i did on those legs. considering what i had around the house, i don't think there's a doctor who could have done any better.}
<A>__{and now suddenly she flicks off the blankets, uncovering his body.}
